1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:04,526
Some workflows are much easier to demonstrate than to describe.

2
00:00:04,526 --> 00:00:09,855
Teach turns one visible demonstration into a reusable Codex skill.

3
00:00:10,300 --> 00:00:18,421
It is an open-source Codex plugin built for OpenAI Build Week with Codex and GPT-5.6.

4
00:00:20,300 --> 00:00:21,986
Naming is optional.

5
00:00:21,986 --> 00:00:26,578
Teach can infer it later, but recording never starts from the first request.

6
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:40,578
A separate ready action creates a short-lived consent record and starts this computer's native recorder.

7
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:45,250
I perform the task normally.

8
00:00:45,250 --> 00:00:52,500
Teach captures the screen and pointer locally, with no raw keystroke log and no hidden background monitoring.

9
00:01:05,300 --> 00:01:13,736
Now the configured Codex model reads bounded frames, structures the goal and steps, and checks which actions Codex can actually replay.

10
00:01:13,736 --> 00:01:17,815
The live status makes longer analysis visibly active.

11
00:01:18,300 --> 00:01:20,750
This is more than record and replay.

12
00:01:20,750 --> 00:01:31,565
Teach labelises the process: goal, software, duration, risks, output contract, ordered steps, and capability-based replayability.

13
00:01:42,300 --> 00:01:44,184
The model only drafts.

14
00:01:44,184 --> 00:01:48,263
I can review and edit what it learned before anything is published.

15
00:01:57,300 --> 00:02:06,947
Optimization is optional, and it is strict: an alternative must target the exact same output, not a cheaper or lower-quality substitute.

16
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:16,223
Once approved, Teach publishes a normal portable skill.

17
00:02:16,223 --> 00:02:19,157
I can call it directly from a new Codex task.

18
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:38,921
Teach is Apache-2.0, stores inspectable files instead of a hidden database, and packages native paths for Linux, macOS, and Windows 11.

19
00:02:41,300 --> 00:02:45,460
OpenAI Record and Replay validates the interaction.

20
00:02:45,460 --> 00:02:51,921
Teach makes the idea open, cross-platform, richly labeled, and user-reviewable.

21
00:02:51,921 --> 00:02:53,605
Show Codex once.

22
00:02:53,605 --> 00:02:54,736
Keep the skill.
